HB 599 Original 2026 Regular Session Schamerhorn
Abstract: Prohibits the sale of running surface water belonging to the state for use in other
states.
Present law provides for the management of running surface water of the state including the
establishment of cooperative endeavor agreements for withdrawal and sale of the water.
Present law authorizes the secretary to enter into cooperative endeavor agreements for use
of running surface water outside of the boundaries of the state with the approval of the
House Committee on Natural Resources and Environment and the Senate Committee on
Natural Resources.
Proposed law revokes the authority to enter into cooperative endeavor agreements for use
of running surface water outside of the state and further provides that no provision of present
law can be construed to allow the sale of the running surface water of the state for use
outside the state.
(Adds R.S. 30:961(L); Repeals R.S. 30:961(I))
